HEADWORD: Jaghir
<hw>Ja"ghir</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Per.
<ets>j⟦amac⟧g⟦imac⟧r</ets>.]</ety> <def>A village or district the
government and revenues of which are assigned to some person, usually in
consideration of some service to be rendered, esp. the maintenance of
troops.</def> <altsp>[Written also <asp>jaghire</asp>, <asp>jagir</asp>,
etc.]</altsp> <mark>[India]</mark> <rj><au>Whitworth.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
